@startuml Option2_MethodBased_Overview

title Option 2: Method-based ParameterSet Distribution (mw::com IPC)

participant "ConfigDaemon" as ConfigDaemon
participant "ParameterSetCollection" as PSC
participant "mw::com Skeleton\n(InternalConfigProviderInterface)" as Skeleton
database "Shared Memory\n(pre-allocated, max payload size)" as SHM
participant "mw::com Proxy\n(SemiDynamicSingleInstantiationStrategy)" as Proxy
participant "Polling Thread" as Poller
participant "ParameterSet Cache" as Cache
participant "ConfigProvider" as CP

== Initialization ==

ConfigDaemon -> Skeleton : Create(instance_specifier)
ConfigDaemon -> Skeleton : RegisterHandler(get_parameterset)
Skeleton -> SHM : register shared memory region for method call
SHM --> Skeleton
Skeleton --> ConfigDaemon


note over Proxy
    additional_shm_size_bytes = meta info + max ParameterSet payload + max ParameterSet name length
    all of which can be estimated statically at compile time
end note

CP -> Proxy : Create proxy via\nSemiDynamicSingleInstantiationStrategy\n(additional_shm_size_bytes)
Proxy -> SHM : map into proxy's shared memory region
SHM --> Proxy
Proxy --> CP


== Runtime: GetParameterSet ==

ConfigDaemon -> Skeleton : OfferService

    CP -> Proxy : get_parameterset.Allocate()
    Proxy -> SHM : allocate ParameterSetName buffer
    SHM --> Proxy : return ParameterSetName buffer
    CP -> Proxy : fill name bytes into ParameterSetName
    CP -> Proxy : get_parameterset(ParameterSetName)
    Proxy -> SHM : write request into shared memory
    SHM -> Skeleton : method handler invoked
    Skeleton -> PSC : look up ParameterSet by name
    PSC --> Skeleton : serialized ParameterSetContent\n(or kParameterSetNotFoundContent)
    Skeleton -> SHM : write ParameterSetContent into result buffer
    SHM --> Proxy : method returns ParameterSetContent
    Proxy --> CP : Result<ParameterSetContent>
    CP --> CP : parse JSON and return

note over SHM
    A bad usage of the mw::com method with an
    undersized pre-allocated SHM may cause a
    runtime memory issue if the actual payload
    exceeds the estimated max size.
end note

@enduml
